{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772546769,"nonce":"KVb+n7QbMSkz0I9DM/mjM+0aJic=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vbJTl","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/331","origin":"github"},"title":"Convention: use pkg: labels in multi-package repos","message":"## Summary\n\nMulti-package project repos (e.g., `unh_marine_simulation`) make it hard to tell which\npackage an issue targets. Adding `pkg:\u003cname\u003e` labels solves this — issues can be filtered\nby package, and multi-package issues get multiple labels.\n\n## Convention\n\n- **Prefix**: `pkg:` followed by the ROS package directory name\n- **Color**: consistent across all package labels in a repo (e.g., `#5319E7`)\n- **Description**: short phrase describing the package's role\n- **Scope**: one label per package found via `package.xml`; create labels when the package is added to the repo\n\n### Example (unh_marine_simulation)\n\n| Label | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `pkg:asv_helm` | ASV helm controller |\n| `pkg:asv_sim` | ASV dynamics simulator |\n| `pkg:asv_sim_msgs` | ASV sim message definitions |\n| `pkg:marine_simulation` | Simulation launch and config |\n| `pkg:mbes_sim` | Multibeam sonar simulator |\n| `pkg:vrx_project11` | VRX competition integration |\n\nThese labels have already been created and applied to open issues on\n[unh_marine_simulation](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_simulation) as a pilot.\n\n## Adoption\n\n- Apply to all multi-package project repos in the workspace\n- Add guidance to `.agent/templates/` or `AGENTS.md` so agents create package labels\n  when setting up a new project repo\n- Optionally automate label creation from `find . -maxdepth 2 -name package.xml`\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}